name: pheochromocytoma
descr: An endocrine organ benign neoplasm that arises within the adrenal medulla, releasing epinephrines and norepinephrines hormones that cause either episodic or persistent high blood pressure.

name: agammaglobulinemia
descr: A B cell deficiency that is caused by a reduction in all types of gamma globulins.
